Subject: Re: [VB] Sump

Besides the benefits of no oil starvation in hard cornering, the crank never
has to spin in a puddle of oil.  There is a slight gain in HP from the lack of
the crank splashing in the oil sump.

Steve

> People claim that a dry sump system give a HP boost over regular oil pan
> systems, but I cannot explain why.  Probably negligible in a non racing VW.

